<Author>CanadianTravellers2
<Content>Outrigger Reef is a 10 plus..an excellent beach resort property! To all traveller's considering The Outrigger Reef..you cannot go wrong..no exaggeration..everything is perfect here. Our family has been coming here since 1979 when the property was known as Cinerama Reef. Through the years we have been loyal guests..seen changes in the 80's and 90's but none as positive as now. The newly renovated property is immaculate. I had booked 2 rooms for my partner and myself and another for my parents which had their 50th wedding anniversary here , celebrated during our stay. We were graciuosly both upgraded to oceanfront rooms. In all our years of coming here we have stayed in a variety of rooms in both towers (Ocean Tower and Pacific Tower)but have never had a room category higher than oceanview ,which by the way are beautiful rooms as are the partial and cityview too. All I can say is the Oceanfront room in the OceanTower is absolutely worth it. Book this room if you wish the best directly on Waikiki Beachroom experience. Leave the balcony doors open and sleep to the sounds of the waves..wake up to the most beautiful sunrise and in the evening , when others walk to the beach to view the incredible sunsets , you just step out on your oceanfront balcony and take it all in.The property after all its renovations is 5 star. Excellent attentive service/staff , at the check in to the room attendants to dining room staff. The shops and facilities are very good. It was so refreshing to have the feeling that the staff really care about you and not just on the surface. Whenever we walked by the checkin staff looked up , waved or said hi. The same with the room attendants in the hallway, always greeted you warmly.Same with the pool attendants that give you towels..very courteous and helpful. The lounge chairs with mats on them very relaxing and the new pool and hotubs/whirlpool nice. I think the only part left to still finish renovation is the Serenity Spa and new poolside restaurant. Will look forward to these on our return. 
