<Content>Beautiful room and superb service For the last two days of my family's stay in Hawaii we stayed at an oceanfront room at the Outrigger on the Reef. The hotel room was exquisite and had superb extras like being able to call to the mainland for free. Even though we didn't spent much time in oor room, the room was newly and pleasantly appointed. The small lanai off the room was just right for enjoying a late night cocktail or an in room breakfast.The hotel staff was terrific from the bellmen, the valet parking staff, the front desk staff and restaurant employees. Everyone was pleasant, quick to answer any questions you had and always smiles on their faces.I really was pleased to find out the hotel had a Hawaiian Airlines kiosk downstairs in their business center . We were able to check in the morning we left. This made the line at the airport exceptionally quick as all we had to do was drop off our luggage and show our boarding passes at the Hawaiian Air luggage drop.There's alot of construction going on in front of and across the street from the hotel, but the only time the noise was really noticeable was when you were at the hotel entrance or on the beach. Part of the construction is going on at the hotel itself; the other construction is the 463 for sale, fee simple condos being built across the street....by Donald Trump.The only drawbacks, and these are of no fault of the hotel, were the rude individuals staying in the rooms nearby who allowed their hotel room doors to repeatedly slam shut at 5 am.The other drawback were the individuals who stood out on their lanai's (even though the state laws/hotel rules are written clearly in each room) smoking cigarettes. The hotel's policy/Hawaiian state law note that public spaces (hotel rooms included) and on the hotel website, that smoking in the hotel rooms and lanai's is strictly prohibited. Apparently there are some hotel guests who cannot read or think they're above it all and have the right to stink some of us