<Content>remodeled part great. My wife and I got into Oahu 1 day earlier than expected and decided to stay here before moving to the Outrigger Regency on Beachwalk. We booked a partial ocean view room and got room 711.The room was absolutely fantastic. It looked like we were the first ones to stay in the room. Every single inch has been redone. The shower and toilet were in a seperate room and all new. Outside was a huge vanity area that had a referig and a partial wall that seperated the bath area from the bedroom area, and the wall had wood louvers that you could open and close. The king sized bed was spectacular and comfortable. There was a chaise lounger that actually opened up to a bed. There also was a table, desk, and 2 chairs. The balcony had 2 sliding doors, but no screen. The view was fantastic.We enjoyed our spacious room so much we cancelled our second stay at the Outrigger Regency Beachwalk and booked a full ocean view room. We were not as excited with our second room.We were given a room on the 10th floor, the very top. The elevators only go up to the 9th floor, but there is a service elevator around the corner that goes up to a landing between the 9th and 10th floor. You then have to take a half flight of stairs up to the 10th floor. No problem. Our room was 1010. This room was EXTREMELY narrow. Where the other room had the spaciousness, especially in the bath area, this room was tight and cramped. We were told this was the trade off in getting an ocean view room.This room had 2 twin beds with just barely enough space between the ends of the beds and the dresser to walk by. The bathroom vanity was against the wall where the louvers were in the other room and a small closet was to the side. The shower/toilet was the same. This room also had the 2 sliding doors with no screens, but the balcony on this floor was twice as deep as the other room. It had a full size table and 4 chairs on it. The other only had 2 chairs and a small table. The view of Diamond Head from the 10th floor was amazing. There was a desk with 1 chair. The second chair was up against the wall by the bed. There was no table or place to sit at besides on a bed.The view of the pool construciton was not so amazing. In order to compensate, Outrigger is offering a $100 dining voucher for stays of 3 nights or longer. We were told that since we had a discounted rate on our room (for 4 nights) we could not have the voucher. I overheard the person next to me checking in being discouraged from trying to use it, or even take it with him. This really rubbed me the wrong way. Also, only valet parking is available for $25/day. The valet guys were great, but I didnt like not having access to my car.We did use a courtesy room in the old, old tower after we checked out and that worked out great. The internet did not work in our first room but did in the second. It was via cable, but was free.The parts of this place that have been redone are fantastic. There is alot of contruction going on around: the pool area, the tower next to the one that is done, the reception area, stores inside the building. the Ocean House is an absolute fantastic place for a romantic dinner. It is expensive, but the food is out of this world. The kind of place a $100 dining voucher would REALLY come in handy.We enjoyed our stay, and the construction noise was not too intrusive. Next time I dnot know if we will pay for the upgrade to the full ocean view room, based on the smaller size. 
