<Content>Rave Reviews for The Reef On the Beach we stayed for 4 days at the Outrigger Reef and loved it. we had a partial sea view room that was huge!! Our room was spotless and had all the comforts you need (dressing table, shower, hairdryer, tv, safe and balcony with furniture) the hotel is open plan with no windows or doors and it had such a lovely relaxed feel. Check in was quick and we were upgraded because we were away for our wedding anniversary. every morning fresh lei (flowers) were placed in our room. There was a reasonably sized pool and 4 places to eat. we had breakfast (buffet style but you can pick your meat and request how you want it cooked) in the restaurant right by the beach and had the delight of watching a beautiful morning wedding ceremony take place on the Waikiki beach. as you would imagine there was a great variety for breakfast with so much fresh fruit its unbelieveable. also cereals, cooked meat, yoghurts, breads etc..the beach was right on the hotel's doorstep and went on for miles. lots of nice clean sand and also a playground on grass for the children. to the right of the hotel you get a fabulous view of Diamond Head Crater. we had dinner in the restaurant overlooking the beach. the food was out of this world. the waiter was so friendly and gave us tips on what to do/see and also where else to eat on the island. im vegetarian and found i had a good choice off the menu. each morning we would come down to breakfast to see different activities taking place - basket weaving, lei making, hula dancing etc.. the children loved it. we had hired a car from the airport but did find th edirections a little confusing getting to the hotel(dont drive in Honolulu at rush hour - mad!) and even more bizarre trying to get out of the city. The hotel has valet service. the only downside to our stay was the weather. we were there 4 days and it rained for 3 of them. but if you visit you must go to the Polynesian cultural centre and Byodo-in temple is worth a