<Author>M123456
<Content>Old but clean, nice location but noisy We stayed at the this hotel from November 22 - 26, 2006.We booked this hotel through hotwire which meant we did not learn the hotel's name until we paid for it. Usually we end up with good hotels when we book through hotwire but this time I was truly scared after reading the Reef reviews on this web site.The Outrigger Reef has a great location. It is within walking distance of all the Waikiki restaurants and shops. It is right on the beach. There are some rocks in the water so water shoes would be a good idea.The staff was friendly and helpful. We ate at the Reef for Thanksgiving and the food was good. We also ate at the breakfast buffet which was not worth the money.The room was out of date decor wise. The shower and bathroom were extremely small. However the room was clean - it was not as bad as I expected from reading the reviews. I imagine some rooms are in better shape than others.The most important thing for visitors to know is that there are three construction projects going on around the Reef. Directly across the street the Embassy Suites is being built. According to the front desk staff construction on this will be done by the end of the year. The second is also across the street from the Reef. This is the Trump Towers. They just started that project so it has a long way to go. The third is on the Reef itself. They have completely gutted one of their building (the one closest to the ocean) and are in the process of renovating it. Our room was a partial ocean view and faced the construction on the Reef which was the most noisy from our location. Luckily we were there over Thanksgiving so construction was at a minimum. This hotel is old and dated but friendly and clean. It has a great location. If construction noise bothers you I would suggest staying somewhere else. 
