<Content>We didn't know about the construction noise... We stayed at the Outrigger Reef on the Beach (ORB) from 11 - 14 September, 2006 as the final part of our Hawaiian honeymoon vacation. The main reason for the neutral rating is that there was very noisy construction taking place all day long.The amenities at the hotel are wonderful. The front desk staff and information/tour booking kiosk personnel were all terrific, helpful and pleasant. Certainly, this hotel is a top notch establishment.Our room (king size bed, sofa, mini-fridge) was clean and well kept by the housekeeping staff. We were a little surprised to find how small the bathroom was, however. Also, if any part of the room looked to be older and worn, it was the bathroom.My wife and I enjoy spending time on the beach. I, more than she, also enjoy spending time pool side. The ORB has a very nice pool area. We did not spend any time at all at the pool, however, because construction on one of the hotel towers went on all day and the jackhammer noise was very annoying. I found it amazing that anyone actually paid to have a massage in the spa area by the pool. I can not see how they could possibly relax in that environment.The noise was not much of an issue by the beach. This is probably because of it being a more open area and the surf sounds covered up most of the construction noise.Having arrived in Honolulu directly from a week on Maui, we found Waikiki beach in general to be small, and the beach area in front of the ORB to be especially so.To summarize, we found the ORB to be a very comfortable hotel, well appointed and right in the heart of Waikiki beach and shopping area. Our only hesitation in recommending it has to do with the ongoing construction work. 
