<Content>Just Average - See Why.... I'll start off with the critiques first to give you a glimpse of what to expectThe hotel grounds were nothing short of average. I booked the reservation expecting to stay at a 3-star hotel and that is exactly what I got. The salt water pool was a decent size and so were the two hot tubs. I have absolutely no complaints at all when it comes to the pools.The staff was very friendly. I have been to the neighboring islands on previous trips but since this was my first time in Honolulu they offered many tips, which were very much appreciated.We were checked in swiftly, since there is major construction going on, we were bumped up to a pool view as opposed to the city view (where they're building the new Trump tower). The hotel is in major need of a facelift. The decor is so outdated, I've got to say, it was the ugliest decor I've ever seen. The pale blue reeked everywhere. Believe what you've read about the bathrooms. All of the reviews are pretty accurate about the size and the grime. No matter how much time you scrub that shower, the dingy brown would not come off.The Shorebird sucked! We reserved the buffet breakfast package (highly unadvisable). They served the same thing everyday: same fruit, same cereals, fried rice with celery, portuguese sausage, eggs, bacon, ham or turkey and french toast. While that's fine for the first three days, it made me sick by the fourth day. We also ate there for lunch and the ahi tacos were completely coated in rosemary. Yuck. The sad part is that the Shorebird has a beautiful view of Waikiki beach. The restaurant has so much potential. Nothing a menu-revamp couldn't fix.The spa was wonderful, get a lomi-lomi massage. My friend and I were in pure bliss. It was honestly the best massage I've ever had. 
