<Content>Paradise at the Reef Second leg of our Honeymoon, we were there for ten nights - absolutey fantastic!Don't be put off by the fact that there is construction work going on around the hotel. They are obviously trying to improve on already excellent facilities, and to be honest, it didn't bother us.The staff went out of their way to be helpful and friendly, champagne was bought up to our room 10 minutes after we checked in, and complimentary buffet breakfasts were ours for the duration of our stay.Only downfall was transferring from the airport to the hotel - it cost us $40 in a cab. Take a tip, ask the bell desk to book you on the shuttle for your return to the airport - it was only $18!!!The room was excellent - bright clean with a fanstastic views over the ocean. The bathroom was a little on the small side, but hey! who spends their vacation in the bathroom? It was clean and perfectly functional.Restaurants were of a high standard within the hotel - try the Shorebird for a dinner with a difference where you bbq your own steaks, but beware, as it gets very busy.Try the Aloha lounge for drinks and cocktails in the hotel lobby. Nightly Hawaiin music together with a Hula dancer adds to the atmosphere.Take the trolley tours if you want informative relaxed trips around the island, these come in at $25 pp per day - a fraction of the cost of the tours offered within the hotels, and you see just as much.For shoppers its a double paradise. All the top class designer stores on the main Boulevard, but do wander around the International market as well.All in all an excellent venue. Right on the beach, full of life and highly recommended. 
