<Content>Decent Hotel, but be wary of construction This was my 3rd time staying at a hotel in Waikiki. It was nicer than the first place (can't remember the name as I was only a teenager), and we stayed at the Sheraton on the Beach a few years ago. I don't think the Outrigger Reef is as nice as the Sheraton but it had its appeal. We booked our vacation through American Airlines vacations and chose a moderate room to save money. When we checked in we were given a city-view room, which basically meant we had a great view of all the construction going on across the street. They are finishing up an Embassy Suites and just starting Trump Towers just across from the front lobby. Just as another reviewer said, the back of the hotel on the beach is very peaceful and relaxing. I loved the hotels vicinity to the ocean and the calm waters. Sailboats  catermerans stop just outfront on the hotel beach and you can book rides on them daily. The hotel pool was large and decent, but often crowded and there are 3 hot tubs that were so hot I rarely saw anyone sitting in them for more than a few minutes. We ate at the Chief's Hut once and the Shoreline twice. Both very casual - we saved our big nights out for other places like Hoku's (at the Kahala) and the Hanohano Room (at the Sheraton). Our room in the Pacific Tower was definitely in need of some renovation but it was very clean. I requested two beds and was given that plus a couch that pulled out into another. Perfect as we were 3 female friends sharing the room. The bathroom was very small and only had a shower. Our room had a nice balcony but it was impossible to sit out on it during the weekday because of the loud construction. On the weekends  at night it was fine if one can get over the eyesore of a giant empty lot in front of you. The entire staff at the hotel was extremely friendly and accomodating. I liked the shops in the lobby and I very much enjoyed the calendar of free activities the hotel offers. We tried the Friday morning hula class and had a fun time. We found out that the lobby will begin major renovation/construction on 10/1/06. So be warned about this. Outside of the construction it was fine. We hardly spent any time at the hotel anyway as we were driving all over the island. 
