<Content>Great location but too much construction! We stayed at Outrigger Reef exactly one year ago and it wasn't too bad with little construction. When we went back this year, the construction was terrible!! What a difference from the front of the hotel to the back of the hotel. At the front, it was loud and distracting with the jack hammer's and traffic going on. It wasn't pleasant, I was actually annoyed. On the other hand, you couldn't hear a thing on the beach! It was absolutely relaxing. I suggest you go to the guys with the yellow umbrellas, it's cheaper and you can get up to $10 off for an all day umbrella. When we first checked in, we got a city view. It wasn't too bad, but the rooms were small. Like the other reviews, the bathrooms were disgusting! I don't know if they were dirty or just really old! But we specifically asked for a pools view and were nicely moved the next day. When we were moved, we had a bigger room with a pool view and a partial ocean view. The bathrooms were much bigger but the shower was basically the same. Small and runned down! One night, when me and my boyfriend got back to our hotel, I heard him shout! He saw a huge roach by our trash can! I was seriously disgusted, but I never reported it, due to the nice house keepers! The people were very friendly but the rooms were just not into par! Last year, we stayed at the Ocean's Tower, but that whole tower is closed due to rennovations, so we had to settle for the Pacific Tower. Other than the rooms, we loved the restaurants in Outrigger Reef. We ate breakfast at the Chief's Hut twice, and we loved it! Other people had the daily specials for $5.99 and they were huge portions! We also ate at the Shorebird, they didn't close till 2 in the morning! It was relaxing hearing the ocean while you have dinner. I recommend Paradise Cove Luau! The best sunset views and a pretty good buffet. It's 100 times better than Germaine's! Hanauma Bay was beautiful but really crowded, go there early! We also went to the Polynesian Culture Center, it was really fun, but it was really hot and humid! Other than feeling really sticky, the shows were awesome! Hawaii has the most friendly people and the best food. Would I recommend this hotel to anyone....maybe after the construction is over. Basically, the whole Waikiki is doing construction though! 
