<Author>blondie223
<Content>Great hotel My boyfriend and I stayed at the Outrigger Feb. 11th - Feb. 18th 2006 and had the best time. When we booked the trip a year in advance, we were not aware that Pro Bowl would be there that first weekend. Therefore, when we checked in, they could not upgrade our room, but did send us a bottle of champagne. By Monday though, Pro Bowl fans had left and it was much less busy. We were then able to upgrade our room to an full ocean view and this room was incredible also, thanks to a couple in NY who told us they were checking out the next day and we did end up getting their room. The view and the sounds were incredible. The showers are a little on the small side, but they get you clean. Our room was a nice size room. We had a king size bed and the bed was very comfortable. The staff were helpful and house cleaning on the 6th floor were so nice and kept the rooms very clean. My boyfriend and I did get engaged on this trip, so that made it an even better trip and the staff also gave us a bottle of champagne for that also.Pearl Harbor is definitely worth seeing, it is very moving and a tear jerker. If you have time, take a drive to North Shore, it is also very beautiful and the waves are worth seeing. We also did a ATV tour at Kuahla Ranch another beautiful part of the island and you see where they filmed parts of 50 First Dates, Pearl Harbor, Jurassic Park... The luau at Germaines is also another must. We had so much fun. Especially, on the bus ride there and back. Hope that you get Cousin K as your tour guide for that event, b/c he will have you laughing the whole time. Overall, the Outrigger is a great hotel, the food was wonderful. Go to the Shorebird at least once for dinner, their food is wonderful. We ate at the Chief's Hut for breakfast and that was probably our best breakfast ever. Rooms are clean and well taken care of.We had the best time in Hawaii and are going back for our honeymoon this December!!!! I would recommend this hotel to anyone!!! 
