<Content>Nothing Special... My boyfriend (fionce as of this trip) and I had the best week in Hawaii ever. I'll start off with our hotel and then get to the activities later. We stayed at the Outrigger Reef from April 6th-13th. When booking our trip we told the agent we wanted to stay at the Outrigger Waikiki on the beach, however the night before our flight we realized we were going to be in the wrong hotel. This was extremely disappointing for me bc I had spent the last 6 months reading every review on Trip Advisor for this hotel. I knew exactly what its good and bad points were. When we got there our agent had arranged for us to be moved if we wanted. After going to our room and checking the place out we decided it would be a real pain to move to another hotel. The rooms at the Reef were pretty small, especially the bathrooms but they were clean, which is the most important thing. We saw the maids on our floor on a regular basis and they were awesome, always friendly and happy. There is 3 restaurants in the hotel, we never ate at the formal one, but the other two were good. The breakfast buffet at the Shore Bird was really good. Most of our meals were at restaurants in Waikiki, we never ate at the same place twice. One place I recommend is TIKI's, it's almost straight across the Duke statue. They had really friendly staff and awesome food. We walked down to the Outrigger Waikiki and found it was way more busy than the Reef and also the beach there was so much nicer than the Reef. If you have time to eat Duke鈥檚 I would do so, food and atmosphere are great. The following are the activities we did when we were there: - Ali-Kai sunset cruise (was ok, lot of older people 鈥?we are 22  26, they make a good effort for everyone to have fun, food was good as well), Pearl Harbor/Chinatown tour (definitely wouldn鈥檛 recommend, it was boring and we spent more time waiting in line to get into the museum than time actually spent inside.), Captain Bob鈥檚 snorkel tour (AWESOME, laid back and they take their time teaching you how to snorkel, take you out into the ocean where there鈥檚 a sandbar. The water is only 3 feet deep and this is where you learn to snorkel, they then take you out to a HUGE reef ) Magic of Polynesia Show (Would not recommend, two drinks were $17, the show was not very long), Helicopter ride (Awesome, but not good if you have a weak stomach, got to see the whole island and the pilot was very informative.), Germaine鈥檚 Luau (GREAT, food was amazing, and the bus ride out there was very entertaining, this is something you can鈥檛 miss while in Hawaii.) I think those are the main activities we did. The two best things in Hawaii are the Hawaiians (soo funny and nice) and the cleanliness. I鈥檝e been to Mexico before and it doesn鈥檛 even compare to Hawaii as far as the people, safety and cleanliness. 
