<Author>mom_in_butte
<Content>Great Stay at the Outrigger Reef Just returned tonight from the Outrigger Reef and had a great stay. Not sure why there were some poor reviews before - we found it to be clean and bright, and the staff extremely helpful (same 9th floor housekeeper -she was GREAT!). Like the previous review, we had a Partial Ocean View (highly recommended). We could watch the surfers in the morning and the evening from our balcony. And from our room we could hear the evening music from the Aloha Lounge and had a see the hula dancer - nice touch. We were also on the 9th floor, but not down at the end. I found our bathroom to be quite large, and the shower stall about the same as my standard shower stall at home, maybe a little bigger. A few chips in the sink but otherwise o.k. Only down side I would have to say was the hard bed (wish I would have got the topper). The construction was not a big issue as we were usually up early and they quit by 4:30 or 5:00. Our first two nights were spent at the other end of the beach where even without construction it is MUCH noisier. The Outrigger Reef is away from Kalakua so you don't get the constant hum of traffic, sirens etc. And the beach to the Hilton side of the hotel is huge and sandy if you want to get out of the rocks. One must do is to walk to the Hilton Hawaiian Village (short walk) on Friday night and check out the free show and fireworks. One maybe/maybe not is the Outrigger Catamaran - make sure you get a coupon, barely worth the $20 never mind the $30 they ask without coupon. They will try and talk you into the $5 shaker (+$2 for the drink) instead of the $2 cocktails - big ripoff. Pretty sure it was straight juice - enjoy the ride, forget the drinks. Or have a pop for $1. Still a decent ride on the ocean but only go on a HOT day when the splash of the ocean would be refreshing and fun rather than just cold. Also, wasn't a big fan of the Shorebird, though many are. Very smokey where you cook your meat, and the person at the grill wasn't all that helpful about how to cook the MahiMahi. Maybe just a bad night. We enjoyed the Chief's Hut much better - reasonably priced, music in the evening, by the waterfalls/lagoon. All in all, we really enjoyed our stay - quiet end of the beach, great staff, would love to go back when the beachwalk is done construction. Wouldn't hesitate to stay again. 
