<Author>fakehips
<Content>OMG!! Cant Wait to go back there!!!! OKAY................This is MY TWO LITTLE CENTS....about staying at The Reef! Loved it, Loved it ,Loved it!!! Let me tell you, Me and my Aunt stayed at the Reef over the Labor Day weekend Holiday.......from the 4th-7th.  With our package, we had a FULL OCEAN VIEW ROOM.......which was OUTSTANDING!!!!!! Actually, breathtaking.....recommend this to ANYONE, spend the extra and go for it.......omg! We were on the fifth floor....and to put it into perspective, we were right above where that lady plays the ucalaley (sp) and teaches the hula. Because we were on the 5th floor, we slept EVERY NIGHT with the sliding glass doors open, and my Aunt ( who is a recent widow from April), laid in the bed close to the doors, and EVERY morning, said she just couldnt get enough of the LOUD waves coming from the ocean. Its was so relaxing. We also had the Big Kahuna package, which including several little knick knaks and a tote, and a cd, little things like that, but the Big Kahuna for me was the breakfast buffet that came with the package! OMG! Shorebird Bar is right down stairs, and yes, its true.........is open and right on the beach, and there is EVERYTHING you could imagine to eat.and eat to your hearts content! They have this thing where they give you this reserve sign, and you find a table thats empty and put it on there, and go fix your plate! Even though its ALL open, with birds fly around LITERALLY...........try to get a table thats right by the openess of the beach! NOTHING like it! We ate beachside EVERY DAY....maybe we were lucky, people we always either leaving, or it was empty, and the place was ALWAYS packed!!! Actually, we ended up having extra tickets for 2 days for 2 people, and when we were waiting for the shuttle back to the airport, we looked for people just arriving, and we gave them away! We couldnt bare them to go to waste!We did the Germaines Luau....too funny! The 2 1/2 hr cruise thingy....nice views, but too rokcy of a ride for me....we only went becasue it has activites to do, and my aunt wanted to learn how to make leas (sp)..... Actually......theres this little mall that you walk through to get to the ship, and I would have REALLY like to have stopped there and shop, because I saw some stuff that I would have boaught in one of the windows of a store, but we had to hurry to catch the transportaion back to the hotel! Lastly, we .......yes we did..........went to see Don Ho!!!! I know, I know......we went for a laugh.....but actually, the man has recently been sick and he came down before the show and took pictures with the people and went back to his hotel...It was at the Wakiki Beachcomber. But the show WAS entertaining, but would ONLY recomend if youve had a couple a drinks and have nothing else to do.lolYes, there was contsruction, but not at the hotel when WE stayed. There was construction down the street, and around the corner by the ABC, but it didnt bother us. Thw reason why WE liked it so much, is beacuse its so centrally located to EVERYTHING. My aaAunt has had a quadruple by-passs, and I PURPOSELY wanted to stay somewhere, that when we HAD to walk, AND YOU DO..................that we were right in the thick of it all! And, All the designer shops, it reminded me of Michigan Ave in Chicago, as Im from Illinois!. Aunt C didnt complain, when she wanted to rest from walking, we just sat down.and shes 65, and the short walks to and fro didnt bother her ONE BIT!So, Im telling YOU ALL THIS..Im looking at my calender to determine WHEN Im going back there...I would stay nowhere else for the value....Im saving my pennies NOW, cause Im going back to the Reef.....but once again, GET AN OCEAN VIEW ROOM!!.....include it when you are planning, dont even THINK about upgrades!!! Even if you have to cut out some other activity exspense, if you put it in the budget from start, I promise you , you WONT be disappointed! ITS A SLAM DUNK! I dont think I would enjoy myself with ANYTHING less, cause you can ALWAYS hang out in the room,(see, we didnt have nor want an agenda), and look at the spectacular view, that will just blow you away!!!!! And the staff was VERY friendly..conseirge was wonderful! 
