<Content>Very Nice Stay at the Outrigger Reef My boyfriend and I came back from a stay at the Outrigger Reef - we were there for six days. We booked our hotel and air through Orbitz so we went for the cheapest room. This gave us a room with no lanai (balcony) and our view was of the building next door. We didn't mind too much - but a lanai would have been nice to air out our swimsuits and towels. The room wasn't terribly big but it had everything we needed and was clean. I wish our bathroom would have had a bath (only shower) but we didn't spend much time in our room.I loved the fact that our hotel was right on the beach. Our #1 tip would is to book a hotel that is on the beach. Even hotels that are 5 or 10 minutes walk from the beach can't compare. Plus you would have to walk through the city with all of your stuff. The shops and restaurants of the Outrigger Reef were great. We had the breakfast special of $4.99 one morning and the breakfast buffet of $9.99 at the Shorebird. We also chose to grill our own meat at the Shorebird one night which was fun - plus it was right on the beach which had a great view.The location of the hotel was great as it was on the beach, between hotels and easy to walk to shopping. It wasn't as crowded which was great. Plus, it was a short walk to the Hale Koa snack shop and the Hilton Village. the Hilton Village was great to visit b/c of the penguins, flamingos, shopping. they also have fireworks every friday night and we saw people outside on the beach there with fire poi which was fun to watch. there were a lot of fun activites right outside the hotel for the beach - we kayaked and rode one of those large sea bicycles.Plus, the location of the hotel is near public transportation which we used to get to Diamond Head and the Ala Moana shopping center. The staff was extremely helpful and courteous. We had a great stay.Tips:1. Book a hotel on the beach!2. Pack sunblock!3. Buy a beachtowel there - they are not expensive and you can find them at the many ABC stores. they also have cheap inflatable rafts.4. We went on the North Shore tour with the Oahu Nature tours and it was fantastic. Plus it wasn't expensive.5. The Shorebird breakfast is very good. 
