<Content>Old Hawaii Alive  My partner and I stayed at the Reef 4 nights, May 17 - 21. We stayed there 30 years ago and, though we've been to Hawaii many times since, never went back to the Reef. I'm glad we did!The Reef has the feel of old Hawaii about it, how things used to be before corporations began designing hotels. The lobby and shopping arcade has been renovated, but you have the feeling of an older, grand hotel.We had a partial ocean view room = very large and spacious with a decent size lanai. The bathroom was small, only big enough for 1 person at a time. The shower was huge, though. The amenities were quite nice.Yes, there is construction across the street. Yes, I did hear jack hammers going for 5 - 10 minutes at a time maybe once a day. But I tuned it out and it never really bothered either of us.The beach is right outside your door. I found it rocky so I moved down in front of the Royal Hawaiian where I snorkeled with green sea turtles. Awesome!Ate at the Chef's Hut for breakfast (daily special $4.95) and had dinner there once - all just fine and with a beautiful setting.I would recommend this hotel and plan to stay there again on my next visit. 
