<Content>Very Good This was our first big holiday together and we were a little nervous after reading some of the bad reviews. No offence but we found most of the bad reviews were by Americans who maybe have a better hotel standard that British people, things such as ice trays don't really concern us but it seems to be a big things with Americans... We booked a standard room and when we got there I cheekily asked for a free upgrade and was told it was $60 a night for a partial ocean view, we declined and he said he would try and get us a good standard room. When we got in our room the balcony was at the side of the hotel but at the end of the block so we got a good view of the beach from there, we were very pleased with that! The sand outside the beach is quite harsh, nice, but definately not soft! and the water is about 3 feet deep for about half a mile out, all dead coral and rock, we went in and were very dissapointed and came out with a couple of cuts.... I'm led to believe that is you walk a half mile to your left or right the water is a lot nicer as they have dug up all the rock. It really is NOT worth going for a swim immediately outside the hotel, although it is good for paddling and the kids to play in for a good 5 or 6 meters befor it gets rocky.The hotel has a good selection of shops, all reasonably priced, although if you walk into town and go in an ABC store (they are everywhere) you will find a better and cheaper selection of everthing you could ever want!The restaurants in the hotel are ok. I say that becuase of the following, the Shorebird has a great breakfast!!!! nice enough lunch, but it is the evening meal we struggled with. You buy a piece of meat and cook it yourself on these big grill things... it was fun and the meat was the best i have ever tasted, but after a long day we did not want to cook our own meal.... and the heat from the grills is eyewateringly hot! not a pleasant experience when the wind blows your way! also no real butter, only creamed butter which sounds nice but doesn't taste that nice!The restaurant next door, cant remember ther name, we went there once and didn't think much of it, quite expensive and everything was served with mashed potato, not a place for children at all!!! the food is for older people who want a nice meal in a nice restaurant but something that doesn't taste brilliant, didn't go back!We did not fancy the place near the pool, looked a bit dirty... drinks from there were nice tho! and quick service...All in all a great holiday! Recommend going to the big island volcano tour!!!!BIG RECOMMENDATION!!! - DON'T TAKE ANY T-SHIRTS!! YOU CAN BUY ABOUT 5 OF THEM FOR 10 AND VERY NICE QUALITY! ASO CHEAP SHORTS AND EVERYTHING! TOWELS VERY CHEAP ALSO!!Email me if you want any info gemmaadair@blueyonder.co.uk 
